<subSubSection pageId="125" pageNumber="126" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="125.[151,1437,1317,2028]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1497,1523]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Teleoconch subcylindrical, with increase in diameter from posterior end to aperture. Surface smooth, semi-translucent white in color. Septum mucronate, pronounced, but flattened and angled away from dorsal margin. Mucro low, heel-like, and usually covered by septum. Aperture rather ovate and oblique. No varix. Periostracum thin, smooth, translucent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="126" lastPageNumber="127" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="125.[151,1437,1317,2028]" lastBlockId="126.[151,1437,150,357]" lastPageId="126" lastPageNumber="127" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1641,1667]" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Description.</emphasis>
Protoconch multispiral (about 2.2 whorls), planispiral, smooth (
<figureCitation box="[1084,1204,1641,1667]" captionStart="FIGURE 109" captionStartId="126.[151,250,1850,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1103,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-170@126.[151,1435,1103,1826]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURE 109. Caecum lightfootanum sp. nov. shells at different growth stages. A. Protoconch and teleoconchs I to III (SBMNH 637735). B. Teleoconchs III to IV (SBMNH 637735). C. Surface of teleoconch I (SBMNH 637735). D. Teleoconch V (SBMNH 637735). E. Surface of teleoconchs II to III (SBMNH 637735). F. Surface of teleoconchs IV to VI (SBMNH 637734). G. Teleoconch VI (SBMNH 637734)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402589" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402589/files/figure.png" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Fig. 109A</figureCitation>
), transition to teleoconch I marked by well-defined apertural varix (
<figureCitation box="[689,807,1677,1703]" captionStart="FIGURE 109" captionStartId="126.[151,250,1850,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1103,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-170@126.[151,1435,1103,1826]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURE 109. Caecum lightfootanum sp. nov. shells at different growth stages. A. Protoconch and teleoconchs I to III (SBMNH 637735). B. Teleoconchs III to IV (SBMNH 637735). C. Surface of teleoconch I (SBMNH 637735). D. Teleoconch V (SBMNH 637735). E. Surface of teleoconchs II to III (SBMNH 637735). F. Surface of teleoconchs IV to VI (SBMNH 637734). G. Teleoconch VI (SBMNH 637734)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402589" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402589/files/figure.png" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Fig. 109A</figureCitation>
). Teleoconch I short, sculptured with axial growth marks (
<figureCitation box="[160,278,1713,1739]" captionStart="FIGURE 109" captionStartId="126.[151,250,1850,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1103,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-170@126.[151,1435,1103,1826]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURE 109. Caecum lightfootanum sp. nov. shells at different growth stages. A. Protoconch and teleoconchs I to III (SBMNH 637735). B. Teleoconchs III to IV (SBMNH 637735). C. Surface of teleoconch I (SBMNH 637735). D. Teleoconch V (SBMNH 637735). E. Surface of teleoconchs II to III (SBMNH 637735). F. Surface of teleoconchs IV to VI (SBMNH 637734). G. Teleoconch VI (SBMNH 637734)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402589" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402589/files/figure.png" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Fig. 109C</figureCitation>
), transition to teleoconch II marked by incised axial line (
<figureCitation box="[946,1067,1713,1739]" captionStart="FIGURE 109" captionStartId="126.[151,250,1850,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1103,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-170@126.[151,1435,1103,1826]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURE 109. Caecum lightfootanum sp. nov. shells at different growth stages. A. Protoconch and teleoconchs I to III (SBMNH 637735). B. Teleoconchs III to IV (SBMNH 637735). C. Surface of teleoconch I (SBMNH 637735). D. Teleoconch V (SBMNH 637735). E. Surface of teleoconchs II to III (SBMNH 637735). F. Surface of teleoconchs IV to VI (SBMNH 637734). G. Teleoconch VI (SBMNH 637734)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402589" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402589/files/figure.png" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Fig. 109A</figureCitation>
). Teleoconch II about two times length of teleoconch I, sculptured with numerous, very weak, thin growth lines (
<figureCitation box="[1041,1156,1749,1775]" captionStart="FIGURE 109" captionStartId="126.[151,250,1850,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1103,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-170@126.[151,1435,1103,1826]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURE 109. Caecum lightfootanum sp. nov. shells at different growth stages. A. Protoconch and teleoconchs I to III (SBMNH 637735). B. Teleoconchs III to IV (SBMNH 637735). C. Surface of teleoconch I (SBMNH 637735). D. Teleoconch V (SBMNH 637735). E. Surface of teleoconchs II to III (SBMNH 637735). F. Surface of teleoconchs IV to VI (SBMNH 637734). G. Teleoconch VI (SBMNH 637734)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402589" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402589/files/figure.png" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Fig. 109E</figureCitation>
), transition to teleoconch III marked by incised axial line, followed by increase in diameter (
<figureCitation box="[907,1027,1785,1811]" captionStart="FIGURE 109" captionStartId="126.[151,250,1850,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1103,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-170@126.[151,1435,1103,1826]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURE 109. Caecum lightfootanum sp. nov. shells at different growth stages. A. Protoconch and teleoconchs I to III (SBMNH 637735). B. Teleoconchs III to IV (SBMNH 637735). C. Surface of teleoconch I (SBMNH 637735). D. Teleoconch V (SBMNH 637735). E. Surface of teleoconchs II to III (SBMNH 637735). F. Surface of teleoconchs IV to VI (SBMNH 637734). G. Teleoconch VI (SBMNH 637734)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402589" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402589/files/figure.png" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Fig. 109A</figureCitation>
). Teleoconch III with identical characters as previous stage, transition to teleoconch IV marked by slight incised axial line, followed by increase in diameter (
<figureCitation box="[265,381,1857,1883]" captionStart="FIGURE 109" captionStartId="126.[151,250,1850,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1103,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-170@126.[151,1435,1103,1826]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURE 109. Caecum lightfootanum sp. nov. shells at different growth stages. A. Protoconch and teleoconchs I to III (SBMNH 637735). B. Teleoconchs III to IV (SBMNH 637735). C. Surface of teleoconch I (SBMNH 637735). D. Teleoconch V (SBMNH 637735). E. Surface of teleoconchs II to III (SBMNH 637735). F. Surface of teleoconchs IV to VI (SBMNH 637734). G. Teleoconch VI (SBMNH 637734)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402589" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402589/files/figure.png" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Fig. 109B</figureCitation>
). Teleoconch IV smooth (
<figureCitation box="[670,783,1857,1883]" captionStart="FIGURE 109" captionStartId="126.[151,250,1850,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1103,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-170@126.[151,1435,1103,1826]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURE 109. Caecum lightfootanum sp. nov. shells at different growth stages. A. Protoconch and teleoconchs I to III (SBMNH 637735). B. Teleoconchs III to IV (SBMNH 637735). C. Surface of teleoconch I (SBMNH 637735). D. Teleoconch V (SBMNH 637735). E. Surface of teleoconchs II to III (SBMNH 637735). F. Surface of teleoconchs IV to VI (SBMNH 637734). G. Teleoconch VI (SBMNH 637734)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402589" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402589/files/figure.png" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Fig. 109F</figureCitation>
), transition to teleoconch V marked by slight incised axial line, followed by increase in diameter (
<figureCitation box="[583,709,1893,1919]" captionStart="FIGURE 109" captionStartId="126.[151,250,1850,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1103,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-170@126.[151,1435,1103,1826]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURE 109. Caecum lightfootanum sp. nov. shells at different growth stages. A. Protoconch and teleoconchs I to III (SBMNH 637735). B. Teleoconchs III to IV (SBMNH 637735). C. Surface of teleoconch I (SBMNH 637735). D. Teleoconch V (SBMNH 637735). E. Surface of teleoconchs II to III (SBMNH 637735). F. Surface of teleoconchs IV to VI (SBMNH 637734). G. Teleoconch VI (SBMNH 637734)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402589" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402589/files/figure.png" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Figs. 109B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[719,785,1893,1919]" captionStart="FIGURE 110" captionStartId="127.[151,250,1463,1487]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,633,1439]" captionTargetId="figure-206@127.[151,1435,633,1439]" captionTargetPageId="127" captionText="FIGURE 110. Caecum lightfootanum sp. nov. A. Conceptual reconstruction of growth stages. B. Species distribution map." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402593/files/figure.png" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">110A</figureCitation>
). Teleoconch V with identical characters as previous stage, transition to teleoconch VI marked by suture, followed by increase in diameter (
<figureCitation box="[1072,1192,1929,1955]" captionStart="FIGURE 110" captionStartId="127.[151,250,1463,1487]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,633,1439]" captionTargetId="figure-206@127.[151,1435,633,1439]" captionTargetPageId="127" captionText="FIGURE 110. Caecum lightfootanum sp. nov. A. Conceptual reconstruction of growth stages. B. Species distribution map." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402593/files/figure.png" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Fig. 110A</figureCitation>
). Teleoconch VI (last growth stage) small for genus [Tol 
<quantity box="[545,713,1964,1992]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.625" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.45" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" unit="mm" value="1.625" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.45">1.45–1.80 mm</quantity>
], larger than previous stage, tubular, mildly and regularly arched [Larc: 
<quantity box="[228,395,2001,2028]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.15" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.3" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" unit="mm" value="0.515" valueMax="0.6" valueMin="0.43">0.43–0.60 mm</quantity>
; Arc: 
<quantity box="[463,632,2000,2027]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="9.0" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" unit="mm" value="0.095" valueMax="0.1" valueMin="0.09">0.09–0.10 mm</quantity>
], with increase in diameter from posterior to aperture, semi-translucent white (
<figureCitation box="[228,333,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 108" captionStartId="126.[151,250,983,1007]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,381,959]" captionTargetId="figure-115@126.[151,1435,381,959]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURE 108. Caecum lightfootanum sp. nov. A. Profile view with periostracum (SBMNH 637735). B. Profile view without periostracum (SBMNH 637735). C. Holotype, profile view (SBMNH 637734). D. Paratype, ventral view (SBMNH 637735). E. Paratype, subadult transition, ventral view (SBMNH 637735). F. Operculum, exterior surface (SBMNH 637735)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402587/files/figure.png" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">Figs. 108</figureCitation>
A–C). Surface smooth (
<figureCitation box="[599,713,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 109" captionStartId="126.[151,250,1850,1874]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1103,1826]" captionTargetId="figure-170@126.[151,1435,1103,1826]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURE 109. Caecum lightfootanum sp. nov. shells at different growth stages. A. Protoconch and teleoconchs I to III (SBMNH 637735). B. Teleoconchs III to IV (SBMNH 637735). C. Surface of teleoconch I (SBMNH 637735). D. Teleoconch V (SBMNH 637735). E. Surface of teleoconchs II to III (SBMNH 637735). F. Surface of teleoconchs IV to VI (SBMNH 637734). G. Teleoconch VI (SBMNH 637734)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402589" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402589/files/figure.png" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">Fig. 109F</figureCitation>
). Posterior [Dpe: 
<quantity box="[909,1075,150,177]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.95" metricValueMax="4.4" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" unit="mm" value="0.395" valueMax="0.44" valueMin="0.35">0.35–0.44 mm</quantity>
] with thick edge, squared shoulder (
<figureCitation box="[203,322,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 108" captionStartId="126.[151,250,983,1007]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,381,959]" captionTargetId="figure-115@126.[151,1435,381,959]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURE 108. Caecum lightfootanum sp. nov. A. Profile view with periostracum (SBMNH 637735). B. Profile view without periostracum (SBMNH 637735). C. Holotype, profile view (SBMNH 637734). D. Paratype, ventral view (SBMNH 637735). E. Paratype, subadult transition, ventral view (SBMNH 637735). F. Operculum, exterior surface (SBMNH 637735)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402587/files/figure.png" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">Fig. 108D</figureCitation>
). Septum mucronate, pronounced with flattened top, angled away from dorsal margin (
<figureCitation box="[1306,1424,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 108" captionStartId="126.[151,250,983,1007]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,381,959]" captionTargetId="figure-115@126.[151,1435,381,959]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURE 108. Caecum lightfootanum sp. nov. A. Profile view with periostracum (SBMNH 637735). B. Profile view without periostracum (SBMNH 637735). C. Holotype, profile view (SBMNH 637734). D. Paratype, ventral view (SBMNH 637735). E. Paratype, subadult transition, ventral view (SBMNH 637735). F. Operculum, exterior surface (SBMNH 637735)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402587/files/figure.png" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">Fig. 108C</figureCitation>
). Mucro low, heel-like, positioned on dorsal margin, usually covered by septum.Aperture rather ovate [Da: 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="126" pageNumber="127" unit="mm" value="0.45" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.4">0.40–0.50 mm</quantity>
], oblique, slightly constricted (
<figureCitation box="[542,659,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 108" captionStartId="126.[151,250,983,1007]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,381,959]" captionTargetId="figure-115@126.[151,1435,381,959]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURE 108. Caecum lightfootanum sp. nov. A. Profile view with periostracum (SBMNH 637735). B. Profile view without periostracum (SBMNH 637735). C. Holotype, profile view (SBMNH 637734). D. Paratype, ventral view (SBMNH 637735). E. Paratype, subadult transition, ventral view (SBMNH 637735). F. Operculum, exterior surface (SBMNH 637735)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402587/files/figure.png" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">Fig. 108D</figureCitation>
). No varix. Lip smooth (
<figureCitation box="[930,1048,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 108" captionStartId="126.[151,250,983,1007]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,381,959]" captionTargetId="figure-115@126.[151,1435,381,959]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURE 108. Caecum lightfootanum sp. nov. A. Profile view with periostracum (SBMNH 637735). B. Profile view without periostracum (SBMNH 637735). C. Holotype, profile view (SBMNH 637734). D. Paratype, ventral view (SBMNH 637735). E. Paratype, subadult transition, ventral view (SBMNH 637735). F. Operculum, exterior surface (SBMNH 637735)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402587/files/figure.png" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">Fig. 108D</figureCitation>
). Periostracum thin, smooth, translucent (
<figureCitation box="[234,352,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 108" captionStartId="126.[151,250,983,1007]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,381,959]" captionTargetId="figure-115@126.[151,1435,381,959]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURE 108. Caecum lightfootanum sp. nov. A. Profile view with periostracum (SBMNH 637735). B. Profile view without periostracum (SBMNH 637735). C. Holotype, profile view (SBMNH 637734). D. Paratype, ventral view (SBMNH 637735). E. Paratype, subadult transition, ventral view (SBMNH 637735). F. Operculum, exterior surface (SBMNH 637735)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402587/files/figure.png" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">Fig. 108A</figureCitation>
). Operculum thin, light brown; exterior surface with 5–7 concentric rings (
<figureCitation box="[1177,1291,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 108" captionStartId="126.[151,250,983,1007]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,381,959]" captionTargetId="figure-115@126.[151,1435,381,959]" captionTargetPageId="126" captionText="FIGURE 108. Caecum lightfootanum sp. nov. A. Profile view with periostracum (SBMNH 637735). B. Profile view without periostracum (SBMNH 637735). C. Holotype, profile view (SBMNH 637734). D. Paratype, ventral view (SBMNH 637735). E. Paratype, subadult transition, ventral view (SBMNH 637735). F. Operculum, exterior surface (SBMNH 637735)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402587/files/figure.png" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">Fig. 108F</figureCitation>
). Conceptual reconstruction of growth stages shown in 
<figureCitation box="[619,736,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 110" captionStartId="127.[151,250,1463,1487]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,633,1439]" captionTargetId="figure-206@127.[151,1435,633,1439]" captionTargetPageId="127" captionText="FIGURE 110. Caecum lightfootanum sp. nov. A. Conceptual reconstruction of growth stages. B. Species distribution map." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402593/files/figure.png" pageId="126" pageNumber="127">Fig. 110A</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
